The paper deals with algorithmic problems related to monitoring the performance of large shared computing systems, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. The focus on tracking outliers in a set of streams suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The use of heuristics and simulation suggests that it could also belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the theoretical results and lower bounds suggest that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
